docs.snippet: FRENCH LICK, Ind., July 3 (UPI) -- Mickey Wright matched par 74 today and regained first place in the Ladies' Professional Golfers Association championship by one stroke. She has a 54-hole total of 221 at the Sheraton Country Club course.

docs.lead_paragraph: LIMA, Peru, July 8 -- The Caribbean conflicts that have pushed the American republics to a new foreign ministers' consultation have caused difficulty for the South American nations. Regional ties with the northern states and individual internal political problems affect the attitude of each of the ten South American republics.

byline.original: By JUAN de ONISSpecial to The New York Times

docs.snippet: WARREN, Ohio, July 9 (AP) -- Louise Suggs, the leading money winner on the women's golf tour, fired her third straight sub-par round today for a five-stroke lead in the $16,000 Trumbull open.
